Among nominally significant genes (p &lt; 0.01, uncorrected; no genes passed BH correction at n = 3 vs 3), aducanumab-treated microglia near parenchymal plaques show exploratory signals of chemokine and inflammasome priming (Ccl12, Ifitm3, Nlrp3) and selective metabolic remodeling (Hk3↑, Pfkm↓, Ldhb↓), without engagement of the canonical Itgax⁺ DAM transcriptional program. These patterns are exploratory and require validation in larger cohorts.

